1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,253
[HOMER] <i>Get the meds needed. Go!</i>

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:04,587
<i>We're in a hurry!</i>

3
00:00:05,797 --> 00:00:06,965
<i>You're so clumsy!</i>

4
00:00:07,048 --> 00:00:08,258
[GRUNTS]

5
00:00:08,883 --> 00:00:10,093
[GRUNTS]

6
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:14,848
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [LUNA AND HOMER GRUNTING]

7
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,934
[GUNSHOTS]

8
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,561
<i>- Doc!</i>
- [GUNSHOT]

9
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,356
[IVAN] <i>We need to remove the bullet.</i>

10
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:25,024
<i>You have to trust me, okay?</i>

11
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:29,529
<i>What more do they want? Money again?</i>

12
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:31,531
<i>Wasn't the ransom money they got enough?</i>

13
00:00:31,614 --> 00:00:34,576
<i>You know, I don't care what they're after.</i>

14
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:37,579
<i>What matters is that we get out of here</i>
<i>while we still have the chance.</i>

15
00:00:37,662 --> 00:00:40,081
<i>You don't even care about Sir Liam?</i>

16
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:44,711
<i>Let me remind you, he risked his life</i>
<i>so that we could escape.</i>

17
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:48,965
<i>Liam. Why did you say earlier</i>
<i>that we might be brothers?</i>

18
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:52,635
<i>Because your mother and my husband</i>
<i>had an affair.</i>

19
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:56,014
[EMIL] <i>What was he thinking?</i>

20
00:00:56,097 --> 00:00:58,183
<i>That I wasn't serious about my threats?</i>

21
00:00:58,266 --> 00:00:59,684
<i>I'm sorry,</i>

22
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:01,644
<i>but one of you</i>

23
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:06,691
<i>will have to fall from heaven</i>
<i>and go to hell!</i>

24
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:08,818
<i>Padua, calm down.</i>

25
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:10,820
<i>My men just got stuck inside the hospital.</i>

26
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:13,656
<i>Just look up to the sky, General Cabral.</i>

27
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:19,287
<i>I can finally make you pay</i>
<i>for what you did to my daughter.</i>

28
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:23,083
<i>- He's the one we're going to drop.</i>
<i>- No! Leave my son alone!</i>

29
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,960
[GRUNTING]

30
00:01:26,044 --> 00:01:27,754
<i>Leave them out of this!</i>

31
00:01:27,837 --> 00:01:31,257
<i>Everyone will suffer</i>
<i>because of what you did!</i>

32
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:34,344
<i>I'll teach a lesson not only</i>
<i>to the police,</i>

33
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:35,678
<i>but to you as well!</i>

34
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:44,813
[ECG MONITOR BEEPING]

35
00:01:51,444 --> 00:01:58,368
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:18,513
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

37
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:35,905
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:03:05,768 --> 00:03:09,731
[ECG MONITOR BEEPING]

39
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:11,274
[BULLET CLANGS]

40
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:17,447
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:39,135
[GOON] Hurry!

42
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:46,017
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,485
Hurry! Go there!

44
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:04,911
[COUGHING]

45
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:08,498
[COUGHS]

46
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:12,794
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

47
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:14,629
Hurry up!

48
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,017
Hurry!

49
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,477
Come in! Hurry!

50
00:04:30,853 --> 00:04:32,355
Hurry! This way!

51
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:34,732
Come on! Stand over here!

52
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:39,946
You take care of them.

53
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:42,699
If they escape,

54
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:45,952
you know what will happen.

55
00:04:46,035 --> 00:04:47,036
[GOON] Yes, boss.

56
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:49,747
Sit down!

57
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,958
- I said sit down!
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

58
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:53,251
Now!

59
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:59,507
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:11,311
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:14,605
[LINE RINGING]

62
00:05:14,689 --> 00:05:16,607
[CALL DISCONNECTING]

63
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:18,651
- Dado!
- Yes, sir?

64
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:20,778
- Take Liam away.
- No!

65
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:23,489
- [MAGNUS] Don't!
- [CRYING] Please don't!

66
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:25,158
- [GRETA] Liam!
- Hey, get up.

67
00:05:25,241 --> 00:05:27,410
- Get up!
- No!

68
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:30,163
- No! Olsen!
- [LUCAS] Come on!

69
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:32,582
- Olsen!
- [WENDY] Olsen!

70
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:34,375
- Olsen!
- [WENDY CRYING] Olsen!

71
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:36,044
[MAGNUS SCREAMING]

72
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:39,630
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

73
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:40,923
[LUCAS] Hurry!

74
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:46,846
We can see two hostages now
on the top floor of St. John's Hospital.

75
00:05:46,929 --> 00:05:50,058
It looks like the hostage takers
are planning to push them.

76
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:52,143
Please leave, ma'am.
You're not allowed in here.

77
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:55,063
Sir, please leave. It's dangerous here.

78
00:05:56,731 --> 00:06:02,361
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:06:06,824 --> 00:06:09,035
Cuevas, the megaphone.

80
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:13,247
Sir.

81
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:19,462
[MEGAPHONE BEEPS]

82
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:21,339
[CABRAL] Padua.

83
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:26,052
There are no cops inside anymore.

84
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:27,845
Let them go.

85
00:06:29,388 --> 00:06:30,389
Padua!

86
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:33,643
I'm begging you.

87
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:37,105
Believe me.

88
00:06:39,023 --> 00:06:40,066
Let them go.

89
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:45,696
There are no cops inside anymore.

90
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:48,950
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,409
Believe me!

92
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:54,330
I give you my word.

93
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:56,374
Come on.

94
00:06:58,668 --> 00:07:00,044
Let them go.

95
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:05,174
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

96
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:12,223
[WENDY SOBBING]

97
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:14,684
Well, Magnus Roja?

98
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,146
Are you ready?

99
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:22,233
By the time I count to ten,

100
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:24,902
you should have made a choice.

101
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:29,699
Which of your two sons

102
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,702
are you going to choose to save,

103
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:35,705
and which one will you leave to die?

104
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:40,168
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:42,170
[SOBS]

106
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,337
[EMIL] Well?

107
00:07:45,923 --> 00:07:48,092
If you won't choose,

108
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,762
I'll push them both.

109
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,187
This is only four stories high anyway.

110
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:00,980
The problem is,

111
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:04,108
before they fall to the ground…

112
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:07,069
Boom! They'll explode!

113
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:13,075
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

114
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:22,293
One.

115
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:26,506
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:28,299
Two.

117
00:08:28,382 --> 00:08:29,884
[EMIL CHUCKLES]

118
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:30,885
Liam.

119
00:08:30,968 --> 00:08:32,303
[SOBBING]

120
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:34,305
[EMIL] Three.

121
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,557
Four.

122
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:37,725
Magnus!

123
00:08:37,808 --> 00:08:40,978
What are you waiting for? Save our son!

124
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:44,690
Five!

125
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:50,112
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

126
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:51,614
Why are you hesitating?

127
00:08:51,697 --> 00:08:55,701
Wendy said it herself!
Olsen is not your son.

128
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:58,955
Magnus, Olsen is your son.

129
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:00,665
I'm sorry I didn't tell you.

130
00:09:00,748 --> 00:09:02,917
But Olsen is your son.

131
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:06,128
You're taking back what you said?

132
00:09:06,837 --> 00:09:10,841
- Magnus, don't listen to her!
- Magnus, Olsen's your son!

133
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,510
Olsen, son.

134
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:17,765
I'm sorry I didn't tell you,
but Magnus is your real father.

135
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,643
[WENDY SOBS]

136
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:25,273
- If that's true--
- Six!

137
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:28,067
Is he more important to you than Liam?

138
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:31,988
- [WENDY] Magnus! Have mercy on Olsen.
- [EMIL] Seven!

139
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:36,576
He's served you for years!
You know how much he loves you!

140
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:40,496
[GRETA] Magnus, if Olsen
really is your son, he's a mistake!

141
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,831
[MAGNUS] Okay! Fine!

142
00:09:42,957 --> 00:09:43,916
My life…

143
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:46,919
in exchange for their lives.

144
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:53,384
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:55,553
Wow.

146
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:58,848
What a great father! Hmm?

147
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:01,517
[GRETA SOBBING]

148
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:05,313
But unfortunately for you,
even if you jump off,

149
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:09,483
I'm still going to push both of them.

150
00:10:11,319 --> 00:10:14,238
You've got to make a choice.

151
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:20,244
Only one of them can live.

152
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:23,122
So make your choice.

153
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:28,336
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:29,712
Eight!

155
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:31,756
[GRUNTS]

156
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:34,008
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]

157
00:10:34,091 --> 00:10:35,843
[EMIL CHUCKLES]

158
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,554
Nine!

159
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:42,850
- [WENDY] Magnus…
- [GASPING]

160
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:46,062
- Ten!
- Wait!

161
00:10:46,687 --> 00:10:47,772
Wait!

162
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:55,237
- [GASPING]
- [MAGNUS] Hold on.

163
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:57,990
Wait a minute.

164
00:10:58,074 --> 00:11:03,996
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:18,260
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:21,722
- [MAGNUS] I'm sorry, Olsen.
- [WENDY] No!

167
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:23,766
[CRYING]

168
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:25,768
[LIAM] Wait! Wait! Olsen!

169
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:31,232
- [WENDY SOBS, WAILS] No!
- [GRETA CRIES] Liam!

170
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:34,568
[WENDY WAILS] No!

171
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,195
[SOBS]

172
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:39,198
You're unbelievable, Magnus Roja.

173
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:42,118
You have two firstborns.

174
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:45,287
But don't worry,
I won't kill either of them yet.

175
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:49,500
I can still use them.

176
00:11:54,046 --> 00:12:01,053
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

177
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:08,936
[WENDY CRYING]

178
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:24,702
[WENDY SOBBING]

179
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:28,289
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:30,332
Olsen.

181
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,251
Olsen.

182
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:34,044
Son.

183
00:12:44,763 --> 00:12:49,351
[CACKLING]

184
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,165
Olsen…

185
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:15,586
Why didn't you tell me before?

186
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,672
I'm sorry.

187
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,217
[SNIFFLES] I'm sorry.

188
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,054
Olsen.

189
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:28,891
Son.

190
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:34,021
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:37,441
You know,

192
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,818
Sir Magnus…

193
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:43,656
when I was still a child,

194
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:46,992
all my life,

195
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:52,414
I listened to all your orders.

196
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:56,961
Because I wanted to make you proud.

197
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:01,423
I wanted your approval.

198
00:14:05,469 --> 00:14:09,974
Because ever since I was a kid,
I've seen you as a father figure.

199
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:13,394
But I didn't know

200
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:15,980
that I really was your son.

201
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:22,236
Now that I know,

202
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,863
it feels more painful.

203
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:29,702
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

204
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:32,204
Because now, I know

205
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:37,835
that I don't really matter to you.

206
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:40,880
Olsen,

207
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:42,548
that's not true.

208
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:52,099
I had to choose.

209
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:58,647
You have to understand that.

210
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:02,985
[MAGNUS] I had to choose.

211
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,405
Olsen.

212
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:11,744
Olsen, I hope you
understand why I did that.

213
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:16,081
You too, Magnus.

214
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:20,628
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:21,795
Earlier,

216
00:15:23,213 --> 00:15:27,009
I only said you were Magnus's son

217
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:29,803
because I thought

218
00:15:30,846 --> 00:15:31,680
he might--

219
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,724
He might choose me.

220
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:37,603
He might save me.

221
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:40,439
[MAGNUS] You knew…

222
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:43,275
It's not…

223
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,153
It's not true?

224
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:48,322
[OLSEN EXHALES DEEPLY]

225
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:51,367
[CRIES]

226
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:54,328
Olsen's not your son.

227
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:56,330
[WENDY BREATHING HEAVILY]

228
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:57,581
[OLSEN SNIFFLES]

229
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:01,669
[SNIFFLES] That doesn't matter, Ma.

230
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:06,256
You still won't be able to change the fact

231
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,135
that you…

232
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:16,266
had an affair with Sir Magnus.

233
00:16:18,227 --> 00:16:19,561
[OLSEN SNIFFLES]

234
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:23,065
[OLSEN SNIFFLES]

235
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:26,026
And you, Sir Magnus.

236
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,322
What did I hear earlier?

237
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:34,868
What Emil was talking about.

238
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:39,123
His daughter was one of your victims too.

239
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:44,044
He's Ayen's father.

240
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,716
One of his plans is to get back at me.

241
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:55,264
Because he thinks that
I ruined his daughter's life.

242
00:16:55,848 --> 00:16:57,099
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

243
00:16:57,182 --> 00:17:02,062
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

244
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:03,397
[LOUD THUD]

245
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:09,445
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

246
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,575
[WENDY SOBS]

247
00:17:14,658 --> 00:17:16,452
Olsen…

248
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:20,539
Please forgive me.

249
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:25,669
I'm sorry, son.

250
00:17:32,092 --> 00:17:33,260
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

251
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:39,391
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:46,982
Greta. Liam.

253
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:51,987
I want…

254
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:55,616
I want to apologize to you.

255
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:59,244
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:00,537
[MAGNUS EXHALES DEEPLY]

257
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,124
Just let them be, son.

258
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:12,132
So, Olsen's not my brother?

259
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:17,930
[SIGHS] I'm sorry, son.

260
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:20,682
Because of…

261
00:18:22,559 --> 00:18:24,895
Because of what happened, it only…

262
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:30,109
messed with your head more.

263
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,736
You know, honestly, Pa,

264
00:18:33,403 --> 00:18:35,739
I understand Aunt Wendy.

265
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:39,868
I get why she did it.

266
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:47,668
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:56,969
Boss.

268
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,555
Which of them should we push off?

269
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:05,686
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:10,983
[LUCAS CHUCKLING]

271
00:19:11,066 --> 00:19:12,693
[DADO] Whoa! [CHUCKLES]

272
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:16,405
[LUCAS CACKLING]

273
00:19:18,782 --> 00:19:21,285
[EMIL] You sly bastard.

274
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:25,831
You wanted to kill me?

275
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:27,499
You're worse than me, bastard!

276
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:32,462
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

277
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:34,965
You didn't keep your end of the bargain.

278
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:37,509
We agreed it'd be a simple case
of taking hostages.

279
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:39,595
You'd escape once you got the ransom.

280
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:42,264
No one would get harmed.
But what did you do?

281
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:44,725
You massacred the whole island.

282
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:48,604
Of course, I'd assume that
you would kill me too.

283
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:52,649
So I thought I should beat you to it.

284
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,944
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

285
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,030
I'm sorry, Jericho.

286
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:01,617
[EMIL] My emotions got the best of me.

287
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,744
I wasn't able to tell you.

288
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:06,121
I needed money,

289
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:10,292
but I also had to exact my revenge
against Magnus Roja.

290
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:15,214
He ruined my daughter's life.

291
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,090
My firstborn, Ayen.

292
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:19,593
[EMIL EXHALES DEEPLY]

293
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:22,846
He made my daughter his mistress.

294
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:28,477
He promised her that he'd love her
and give her a good life.

295
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,146
But he left her.

296
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,152
My daughter suddenly disappeared.

297
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:40,405
I don't know where she is.

298
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:42,908
So I'm sorry.

299
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:48,622
Because of my anger toward him,
a lot of people got involved.

300
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:50,832
Even his son and wife.

301
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:57,381
Why don't we just pick him to make
an example of for the cops downstairs?

302
00:20:57,464 --> 00:20:58,840
- What?
- [DADO CHUCKLES]

303
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:02,302
He's useless to us anyway.
Let's push him off.

304
00:21:02,386 --> 00:21:03,679
[JACINTO] Wait, wait.

305
00:21:03,762 --> 00:21:05,138
You still need me.

306
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:10,352
I know…

307
00:21:10,435 --> 00:21:12,104
I know where the loot is.

308
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:14,856
[EMIL] What?

309
00:21:15,816 --> 00:21:18,277
I moved it.
I hid it in a different location.

310
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:21,571
- [EMIL] Smart move.
- [DADO CHUCKLES]

311
00:21:23,156 --> 00:21:24,741
You planned that

312
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:28,120
because you knew we would betray you.

313
00:21:28,203 --> 00:21:30,330
If you kill me,

314
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:34,376
you'll never be able to find
the cash or the jewelry.

315
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:37,838
I'll definitely kill you
if you don't tell us where they are.

316
00:21:37,921 --> 00:21:44,094
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:50,767
[EMIL] <i>Where did you hide the money?</i>

318
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:52,227
<i>- Where?!</i>
<i>- Wait!</i>

319
00:21:52,769 --> 00:21:55,147
<i>That wasn't the plan.</i>
<i>I agreed for my sister, Ayen.</i>

320
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:57,107
<i>Not to let you go on a massacre.</i>

321
00:21:58,817 --> 00:22:00,569
[EMIL] <i>The task is simple.</i>

322
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:04,948
<i>Get our money and jewelry from the island.</i>

323
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:09,369
<i>If you don't return by 12 noon,</i>
<i>we'll kill all of them.</i>

324
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:11,538
[SENATOR MARISTELLA]
<i>Don't abandon us.</i>

325
00:22:11,621 --> 00:22:13,874
[LIAM] <i>We won't, Senator.</i>

326
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:15,375
<i>We will come back.</i>
